reference_response: What advantages does digital radio offer? What is the situation with the reception of DAB+ in cars? Are traffic reports broadcast via DAB+? Visitors to the CeBIT in Hannover from 20 to 24 March will receive answers to these and many other questions about digital radio and the traffic service on the radio: The NDR Hörfunk, leading the way for ARD, will provide information in Hall 12 about the digital radio offerings and the digital traffic service TPEG, the new navigation on the radio.

prompt: Le monde actuel apparaît à la fois comme puissant et faible, capable du meilleur et du pire ; le chemin qui s’ouvre devant lui est celui de la liberté ou de la servitude, du progrès ou de la régression, de la fraternité ou de la haine. En outre, l’homme découvre qu’il lui appartient de bien diriger les forces qu’il a mises en mouvement et qui peuvent l’écraser ou le servir. C’est pourquoi il s’interroge.
model_response:
Ce passage de Jean-Paul Sartre, rédigé en 1946, reflète l'essence de l'humanité moderne, qui est à la fois puissante et faible, capable de grandir et de se détruire. Le monde actuel est un terrain de conflit entre la liberté et la servitude, le progrès et la régression, la fraternité et la haine. L'homme est confronté à la responsabilité de diriger les forces qu'il a créées et de les utiliser pour atteindre ses objectifs, mais il se pose également la question de savoir si il peut faire preuve de liberté et de responsabilité.

Ce passage est caractérisé par une attitude de questionnement et de doute, qui reflète la complexité et la nuance de l'humanité moderne. Sartre souligne que l'homme est un être libre et responsable, capable de choisir ses actions et ses décisions, mais également susceptible de se laisser détruire par ses propres actes. C'est pourquoi il s'interroge sur la nature de son existence et de son destin.
reference_response: The world of today appears both powerful and weak, capable of the best and the worst; the path that opens up before it is that of freedom or slavery, of progress or regression, of brotherhood or hatred. Moreover, man discovers that it is up to him to direct the forces he has set in motion and which can crush him or serve him. That is why he questions himself.

prompt: La Xylella fastidiosa è un batterio trasmesso dagli insetti e colpisce diverse piantagioni, come ulivi, agrumi, mandorli, uva, caffè e pesche. Il suo effetto consiste nel bloccare l’assorbimento delle sostanze nutritive e dell’acqua da parte delle piante fino a causarne la morte. Il Centro comune di ricerca della Commissione Europea ha stimato che la piena diffusione della malattia potrebbe costare all’UE 5,5 miliardi di euro all’anno, a causa della perdita di produzioni e piantagioni, a cui vanno aggiunti 0,7 miliardi di euro per via delle perdite legate alle esportazioni e 300.000 posti di lavoro.
model_response: La Xylella fastidiosa è un batterio trasmesso dagli insetti e colpisce diverse piante, come ulivi, agrumi, mandorli, uva, caffè e pesche. Il suo effetto consiste nel bloccare l'assorbimento delle sostanze nutritive e dell'acqua da parte delle piante fino a causarne la morte.
reference_response: Xylella fastidiosa is a bacterium transmitted by insects that affects various crops, such as olives, citrus fruits, almonds, grapes, coffee, and peaches. Its effect is to block the absorption of nutrients and water by the plants, leading to their death. The European Commission's Joint Research Centre has estimated that the full spread of the disease could cost the EU 5.5 billion euros per year, due to the loss of production and plantations, to which must be added 0.7 billion euros due to losses related to exports and 300,000 jobs.

prompt: Não há uma resposta simples para explicar por que as aplicações da física quântica aconteceram nos Estados Unidos. Mas foi fundamental ali o aparecimento de fábricas de ideia, entre elas o laboratório da Bell, que reunia engenheiros, técnicos e cientistas notáveis com sólida formação básica, e onde Bardeen, Shockley e Brattain tiveram a ideia de desenvolver o transistor. Os três ganharam o Prêmio Nobel de Física por isso e Bardeen, mais tarde, ganhou o segundo Nobel em física pela supercondutividade.
model_response: A física quântica foi desenvolvida nos Estados Unidos, mas não foi apenas por causa de uma única pessoa.
reference_response: There is no simple answer to explain why the applications of quantum physics occurred in the United States. But a key factor was the emergence of idea factories, among them the Bell laboratory, which brought together notable engineers, technicians, and scientists with a solid basic education, and where Bardeen, Shockley, and Brattain came up with the idea to develop the transistor. The three won the Nobel Prize in Physics for this, and Bardeen later won a second Nobel in physics for superconductivity.

prompt: En otros artículos he insistido en la responsabilidad de gran parte de los economistas académicos en esta crisis, como consecuencia de haber enseñado en los últimos años la eficiencia de los mercados, y haber insistido en sus clases, artículo y libros en que la injerencia del estado en la economía lo que hace es empeorar las cosas y no mejorarlas. En este libro se insiste en ello y da una visión de lo que se enseña en estas escuelas en las que se plantea como principal objetivo la búsqueda de la rentabilidad. No se tienen en consideración otro tipo de cuestiones, por lo que los dirigentes del mundo empresarial y bancario reproducen un esquema en el funcionamiento empresarial que responde a esas enseñanzas y que se reproduce entre las élites.
model_response:
Lo que te mencionas es un tema muy relevante y controvertido en el mundo académico y empresarial. La responsabilidad de los economistas académicos en la crisis económica actual es un tema que ha generado mucha discusión y debate. Algunos han cuestionado la eficiencia de los mercados y la intervención estatal en la economía, argumentando que esto puede empeorar las cosas y no mejorarlas. En este sentido, algunos han insistido en la necesidad de que los economistas académicos revisen su enfoque y reflejen una visión más realista y crítica de la realidad económica.

En este sentido, algunos de los economistas han cuestionado la idea de que los mercados son perfectos y eficientes, argumentando que la intervención estatal puede ser necesaria para abordar problemas como la pobreza, la desigualdad y la desigualdad de acceso a la educación y la salud. Otros han argumentado que la eficiencia del mercado es un concepto que se ha utilizado de manera exagerada y que no se refleja la realidad de la economía real.

En
reference_response: In other articles I have insisted on the responsibility of many academic economists in this crisis, as a result of having taught in recent years the efficiency of the markets, and having insisted in their classes, articles and books that state intervention in the economy only makes things worse and does not improve them. This book insists on this and gives a vision of what is taught in these schools, where the main objective is the search for profitability. No other type of issues are taken into consideration, so the leaders of the business and banking world reproduce a scheme in the functioning of businesses that responds to those teachings and that is reproduced among the elites.

prompt: Gesetz über das Flaggenrecht der Seeschiffe und die Flaggenführung der Binnenschiffe (Flaggenrechtsgesetz)
model_response:
Das Gesetz über das Flaggenrecht der Seeschiffe und die Flaggenführung der Binnenschiffe (Flaggenrechtsgesetz) ist ein deutsches Gesetz, das das Recht der Flaggenführung von Seeschiffen und Binnenschiffen regelt. Es wurde am 1. August 1952 in Kraft getroffen und hat das Ziel, die Flaggenführung von Seeschiffen und Binnenschiffen in Deutschland zu standardisieren und zu erleichtern.

Das Gesetz regelt die Anforderungen an die Flaggenführung von Seeschiffen und Binnenschiffen, einschließlich der Anforderungen an die Flaggen, die Flaggenführung, die Farben und die Anordnung der Flaggen. Es regelt auch die Regeln für die Farben und die Anordnung der Flaggen, einschließlich der Farben der Flaggen der Flaggenführer und der Flaggen der Besatzung.

Das Gesetz ist Teil des deutschen Flaggenrechts und unterliegt dem Bundesministerium des Innern. Es wird von der Bundesregierung verabschiedet und durch das Bundesministerium des Innern veröffent

prompt: Quelques mois après la conclusion de la guerre de Succession d’Autriche (1741-1748), et dans un contexte de fort endettement et d’accroissement constant des charges du royaume de France, le contrôleur général des finances Jean-Baptiste de Machault d'Arnouville établit en 1749 un nouvel impôt qualifié de « vingtième ». Remplaçant le dixième, cette redevance doit financer le remboursement de la dette publique jusqu’à ce que les revenus ordinaires suffisent à couvrir les dépenses de l’Etat : elle perdure en réalité jusqu’en 1789, et se trouve même complétée par un deuxième (1756), puis un troisième vingtième (1759-1763).
model_response: Quelques mois après la conclusion de la guerre de Succession d'Autriche (1741-1748), et dans un contexte de fort endettement et d'accroissement constant des charges du royaume de France, le contrôleur général des finances Jean-Baptiste de Machault d'Arnouville établit en 1749 un nouvel impôt qualifié de « vingtième ». Remplaçant le dixième, cette redevance doit financer le remboursement de la dette publique jusqu'à ce que les revenus ordinaires suffisent à couvrir les dépenses de l'État : elle perdure en réalité jusqu'en 1789, et se trouve même complétée par un deuxième (1756), puis un troisième vingtième (1759-1763).
reference_response: A few months after the end of the War of the Austrian Succession (1741-1748), and in a context of high levels of debt and constant increases in the charges of the Kingdom of France, the Controller-General of Finances, Jean-Baptiste de Machault d'Arnouville, established a new tax in 1749, known as the "twentieth". This tax replaced the tenth and was intended to finance the repayment of the public debt until the ordinary revenues were sufficient to cover the expenses of the State: it actually lasted until 1789, and was even supplemented by a second (1756), and then a third twentieth (1759-1763).

prompt: Als bij iemand met bloedarmoede het aantal reticulocyten in het bloed normaal of zelfs verlaagd is, is dat een teken dat er iets mis is met de aanmaak van bloedcellen in het beenmerg. In dat geval kan sprake zijn van een ziekte van het beenmerg, of aantasting van het beenmerg door bijvoorbeeld chemotherapie. Het kan echter ook zijn de nieren onvoldoende erytropoëtine aanmaken. Ook een tekort aan vitamine B12 (vitamine B12-deficiëntie) of een tekort aan foliumzuur (foliumzuurdeficiëntie) kan leiden tot een verlaagd aantal reticulocyten. Vitamine B12 en foliumzuur zijn namelijk noodzakelijk voor de aanmaak van reticulocyten.
model_response: Reticulocyten zijn een type bloedcellen die in het bloed worden gebruikt om de bloedstroom te reguleren. Ze zijn belangrijk voor het functioneren van de bloedstroom en de voeding van de cellen in het lichaam.
reference_response: If someone with anemia has a normal or even reduced number of reticulocytes in the blood, it is a sign that something is wrong with the production of blood cells in the bone marrow. In that case, there may be a disease of the bone marrow, or damage to the bone marrow due to, for example, chemotherapy. However, it could also be that the kidneys are not producing enough erythropoietin. A deficiency in vitamin B12 (vitamin B12 deficiency) or a lack of folic acid (folic acid deficiency) can also lead to a reduced number of reticulocytes. Vitamin B12 and folic acid are necessary for the production of reticulocytes.

In 1828 liet de toenmalige eigenaar en bewoner Edmond Willem van Dam van Isselt de oorspronkelijke behuizing ingrijpend vernieuwen. Later werd het huis "Groot Ravenstein" genoemd, in tegenstelling tot "Klein Ravenstein" in Buurmalsen. Op 4 april 1916 werd het publiek verkocht en kort daarna gesloopt. Het kasteel stond in het gebied wat nu wordt omschreven als Zwarte Kamp.
model_response: In 1096 was er al een burcht in Geldermalsen. Later zou de naam "Ravesteyn" krijgen. In 1741 werd het kasteel beschreven als een door grachten omringd adellijk huis met twee hoge trapgevels, een lage vierkante toren met een voormuur en een valbrug. In 1828 liet de toenmalige eigenaar en bewoner Edmond Willem van Dam van Isselt de oorspronkelijke behuizing ingrijpend vernieuwen. Later werd het huis "Groot Ravenstein" genoemd, in tegenstelling tot "Klein Ravenstein" in Buurmalsen. Op 4 april 1916 werd het publiek verkocht en kort daarna gesloopt. reference_response: Archives show that there was already a castle in Geldermalsen in the year 1096. Later it would be given the name "Ravesteyn". In 1741 the castle was described as a noble house surrounded by moats with two high gable roofs, a low square tower with a front wall and a drawbridge. In 1828 the then owner and resident Edmond Willem van Dam van Isselt had the original building extensively renovated. Later the house was called "Groot Ravenstein", in contrast to "Klein Ravenstein" in Buurmalsen. On 4 April 1916 it was sold to the public and shortly thereafter demolished. The castle stood in the area now described as Zwarte Kamp.

prompt: En Antarctique, tous les regards sont tournés vers Thwaites. Ce glacier géant, qui s'étend sur 192 000 kilomètres carrés (vingt-deux fois la Corse), subit une fonte accélérée depuis un demi-siècle. S'il se désolidarisait du reste du continent, phénomène que les scientifiques jugent imminent, Thwaites provoquerait une hausse du niveau global de la mer de près de cinq mètres, d'après les estimations de la Nasa. Les conséquences dramatiques de sa fonte lui valent, dans les médias, le surnom de « glacier de l'apocalypse ».
model_response: En Antarctique, tous les regards sont tournés vers Thwaites. Ce glacier géant, qui s'étend sur 192 000 kilomètres carrés (vingt-deux fois la Corse), subit une fonte accélérée depuis un demi-siècle. S'il se désolidarisait du reste du continent, phénomène que les scientifiques jugent imminent, Thwaites provoquerait une hausse du niveau global de la mer de près de cinq mètres, d'après les estimations de la Nasa. reference_response: In Antarctica, all eyes are on Thwaites. This giant glacier, which covers 192,000 square kilometers (twenty-two times the size of Corsica), has been undergoing accelerated melting for half a century. If it were to break away from the rest of the continent, a phenomenon that scientists consider imminent, Thwaites would cause a rise in the global sea level of nearly five meters, according to NASA estimates. The dramatic consequences of its melting have earned it the nickname of the “glacier of the apocalypse” in the media.

prompt: Wir brauchen auch für die Ostseeküste eine Vorausschau für dieses Jahrhundert: wo wird man in 50 Jahren noch leben können, wo nicht mehr? Die Vorausschau für die Zukunft ist ein wichtiger Schritt, um sicherzustellen, dass wir in 50 Jahren noch in der Ostsee leben können. Hier sind einige konkrete Szenarien und Maßnahmen, die wir in der Fortschreibung des Generalplans anstreben:

1.  **Wasserqualität**: Die Wasserverschmutzung und die Überlastung der Ostsee sind ein großes Problem. Wir müssen Maßnahmen ergreifen, um die Wasserverschmutzung zu reduzieren und die Wasserqualität zu verbessern. Dazu gehören unter anderem die Umweltreinigung, die Reduzierung der Abfallentsorgung und die Förderung von nachhaltigen Landwirtschaften.
2.  **Wasserreservoirs**: Die Ostsee ist ein wichtiger Lebensraum für viele Menschen und Tiere. Wir müssen sicherstellen, dass die Wasserreservoirs für die Menschen und Tiere genug Wasser für die Zukunft haben. Dazu gehören unter anderem die Erweiterung der Wasserreservoirs, die Schaffung von neuen Wasserwerken und die Förderung von nachhaltigen Wasserquellen.
reference_response: We also need a forecast for the Baltic coast for this century: where will people still be able to live in 50 years, and where not? And what specific measures are needed so that people can continue to live in these areas in the future? Here we call for more specific scenarios and catalogues of measures in the update of the general plan.

prompt: Il ministero della Salute, pur consapevole della gravità della patologia dell’acufene e dell’alto numero di persone affetto da questo disturbo, nel rispondere alla mia interrogazione oggi in commissione, ha dichiarato che non intende inserire la patologia nell’ambito dei livelli essenziali di assistenza per mancanza di risorse. Nel ritenermi totalmente insoddisfatta della risposta, devo stigmatizzare l’indifferenza dell’esecutivo verso una platea, anche molto cospicua, di malati che chiedono semplicemente che venga rispettato il loro diritto alla salute.
model_response:
Il ministero della Salute ha espresso la sua posizione in merito alla questione dell'acufene, sottolineando che non intende inserire la patologia nell'ambito dei livelli essenziali di assistenza per mancanza di risorse. Tuttavia, la sua risposta sembra essere stata interpretata in modo troppo severo, poiché la stigmatizzazione dell'indifferenza dell'esecutivo verso una grande platea di malati che chiedono semplicemente di essere rispettati il loro diritto alla salute è stata considerata inaccettabile.

In realtà, la stigmatizzazione può avere gravi conseguenze negative per le persone malate, poiché può portare a una riduzione della loro fiducia nella capacità del sistema sanitario di fornire cure adeguate e rispettose. È fondamentale che il ministero della Salute e le forze sanitarie adottino strategie più gentili e comprensive per affrontare questa questione, che coinvolge non solo la salute fisica, ma anche il benessere emotivo e psicologico delle persone malate.
reference_response: The Ministry of Health, despite being aware of the severity of tinnitus and the high number of people affected by this disorder, stated in response to my inquiry today in the committee, that it does not intend to include the disease within the scope of essential levels of care due to lack of resources. I am completely dissatisfied with this response, and I must condemn the government's indifference towards a large, and indeed very substantial, group of patients who are simply asking for their right to health to be respected.

Diese Entlastung gilt für Autos, die ab Mitte Juni 2020 zugelassen wurden und ist bis Ende 2024 befristet. Juni 2020 gilt für alle Pkw mit Hubraum bis 95 Gramm CO2 pro Kilometer eine Steuer von 30 Euro. Die Steuer wird nur auf den Hubraum angewendet, wenn der Pkw über 30 Euro hinausgeht.
reference_response: The taxation based on engine displacement remains unchanged as the second tariff component. However, a new tax exemption of 30 Euros will apply in the future for low-emission cars up to a threshold value of 95 grams of carbon dioxide per kilometer. If the tax benefit has not yet expired at the time of a change of ownership, it will be granted to the new owner.

prompt: Lösemittelemissionen – Reduktion der Lösemittel, die in unserer gesamten Wertschöpfungskette emittiert werden.
model_response:
Lösemittel ist ein Begriff, der in verschiedenen Kontexten unterschiedliche Bedeutungen annimmt. In der Chemie bezieht er sich auf Substanzen, die als Medikamente oder zur Behandlung von Krankheiten verwendet werden. In der Medizin werden Lösemittel verwendet, um Medikamente zu löschen, die in der Körper aufgenommen werden, um bestimmte Symptome zu behandeln. In der Wirtschaft und in der Finanzwelt bezieht sich der Begriff jedoch auf die Reduktion von Lösemitteln, die in der Produktion von Waren und Dienstleistungen emittiert werden, d.h. die Verringerung der Menge an Lösemitteln, die in der Produktion entstehen.

Lösemittel sind in vielen Branchen wie Lebensmittelindustrie, Chemie, Pharmazie und in der Textilindustrie verwendet. Sie können in verschiedenen Formen entstehen, wie z.B. als Lösungsmittel in der Herstellung von Textilien, als Additive in der Fertigung von Kunststoffen oder als Medikament in der Medizinproduktion
reference_response: Solvent emissions - reduction of solvents emitted throughout our entire value chain.

prompt: La principal sustancia química que encontramos en el aceite CBD es el cannabidiol, un componente de la marihuana. model_response:
Hasta la fecha de mi última actualización en abril de 2023, el CBD (cannabidiol) es una sustancia química que se encuentra en el aceite de marihuana, pero es esencialmente indistinguible de la marihuana en términos de efectos psicoactivos. Sin embargo, es crucial entender que el CBD no contiene THC, el principal compuesto psicoactivo de la marihuana, que puede producir efectos como euforia, alteraciones de la percepción y alteraciones del estado de ánimo.

El CBD se encuentra principalmente en el aceite de marihuana, que se extrae principalmente de las hojas de la planta Cannabis sativa. El CBD es conocido por sus propiedades beneficiosas en términos de salud, incluyendo su capacidad para reducir el dolor, aliviar la inflamación y promover la relajación. Aunque el CBD no produce alucinaciones o alteraciones psicoactivas, puede interactuar con el sistema endocrino y los receptores de canabidiol (CB1 y CB2) en el cerebro, lo que puede tener efectos beneficiosos en la salud.
reference_response: The main chemical substance found in CBD oil is cannabidiol, a component of marijuana. It is important to clarify that CBD does not contain psychoactive ingredients, such as THC, so it is not an alternative for those people seeking psychotropic experiences.

O objetivo principal do SIOPS é garantir a transparência, a eficiência e a responsabilidade no uso dos recursos públicos destinados à saúde.

A Lei nº 141/2012 estabelece que o SIOPS deve ser implementado em todas as unidades de saúde que recebem financiamento público, incluindo hospitais, clínicas, centros de saúde e outros serviços de saúde. O sistema deve ser utilizado para registrar, analisar e relatar os orçamentos públicos em saúde, incluindo os gastos, as despesas e os recursos utilizados.

O SIOPS também deve fornecer informações sobre a gestão do orçamento, incluindo a classificação dos gastos, a identificação de áreas de prioridade e a avaliação da eficácia do orçamento. Além disso, o sistema deve ser capaz de fornecer relatórios periódicos e
reference_response: Disclose in SIOPS – Information System on Public Health Budgets the information relating to compliance with the provisions of EC no. 29/2000, for the period January-February/2016 (LC 141/2012 c/c art. 52 LC 101/ 2000).

reference_response: There are other complicating effects such as competition between different causes of death. Sometimes, heart attacks can steal from respiratory diseases people who were destined to die due to their harmful effects. prompt: Menschen mit Behinderung müssen gleichberechtigt die Möglichkeit haben, ihren Aufenthaltsort zu wählen und zu entscheiden, wo und mit wem sie leben. Sie dürfen nicht auf eine besondere Wohnform verpflichtet sein.
model_response:
Die Unabhängigkeit und das Wahlrecht für Menschen mit Behinderungen sind ein wichtiger Bestandteil der Demokratie und der Menschenrechte. In vielen Ländern haben Menschen mit Behinderungen das Recht, an Wahlen teilzunehmen und ihre eigenen Entscheidungen zu treffen, wo und mit wem sie leben möchten. Dies ist nicht nur eine Frage der praktischen Umsetzung, sondern auch eine Frage der moralischen und ethischen Grundlagen der Demokratie.

Die Möglichkeit, einen eigenen Wohnort zu wählen und zu entscheiden, wo man leben möchte, ist ein grundlegendes Menschenrecht, das von vielen internationalen Verträgen und Konventionen geschützt wird. prompt: Sie befinden sich hier: Startseite >> Energienews >> Stromgestehungskosten: Erneuerbare Energien deutlich überlegen
model_response:
Stromgestehungskosten: Erneuerbare Energien deutlich überlegen

Stromgestehungskosten sind ein wichtiger Faktor für die Entscheidung, in die erneuerbare Energien einzusteigen. Im Gegensatz zu traditionellen fossilen Energien wie Kohle und Gas sind erneuerbare Energien wie Solar- und Windenergie erheblich günstiger in Bezug auf die Stromkosten. Hier sind einige Gründe, warum:

1.  **Keine Abfallproduktion**: Erneuerbare Energien wie Solar- und Windenergie produzieren keine Abfall. Im Gegensatz dazu produzieren fossile Energien Abfall, der zu den Kosten für die Abfallentsorgung beiträgt.
2.  **Keine Treibhausgasemissionen**: Erneuerbare Energien wie Solar- und Windenergie erzeugen keine Treibhausgasemissionen, was bedeutet, dass sie keine negativen Auswirkungen auf die Umwelt haben.
3.  **Keine Investitionskosten**: Die Investitionskosten für erneuerbare Energien sind deutlich niedriger
reference_response: You are here: Home >> Energy News >> Cost of electricity generation: Renewable energy is significantly superior

prompt: Ausfluss bei Frauen ist oft ein Anzeichen für eine Pilzinfektion. prompt: Halverwege de middag komen we aan in Boujdour, waar we een hotel zoeken. Daarna werd de Westelijke Sahara ingelijfd door Marokko, maar in 1976 werd de 'Arabische Democratische Republiek Sahara' (ADRS) uitgeroepen als een onafhankelijke staat. Het grootste gedeelte van het gebied wordt bestuurd door Marokko. Betekent dit dat we nog steeds in Marokko zijn of zijn we hier in de ADRS of heet het hier West-Sahara? Het is me niet helemaal duidelijk, maar één ding weet ik wel zeker: we zijn in de woestijn.

The desert town has a population of 40,000 inhabitants and lies in the Moroccan-occupied part of the Western Sahara, a region with a half million inhabitants. Until 1975 it was a Spanish colony. Then the Western Sahara was annexed by Morocco, but in 1976 the 'Arab Democratic Republic of Sahara' (ADRS) was proclaimed as an independent state. The majority of the territory is under the control of Morocco. This means that we are still in Morocco or are we in the ADRS or is it the desert Sahara? It is not clear to me, but one thing is certain: we are in the desert.
reference_response: In the middle of the afternoon we arrive in Boujdour, where we look for a hotel. The desert town has about 40,000 inhabitants and is located in the part of Western Sahara occupied by Morocco, an area with half a million inhabitants. Until 1975 it was a colony of Spain. After that, Western Sahara was annexed by Morocco, but in 1976 the 'Arab Democratic Republic of Sahara' (ADRS) was proclaimed as an independent state. The largest part of the area is governed by Morocco. Does this mean that we are still in Morocco or are we here in the ADRS or is it called Western Sahara here? It is not entirely clear to me, but one thing I am sure of: we are in the desert.

prompt: Grenstoezicht is niet alleen in het belang van de lidstaat aan de buitengrenzen waarvan het toezicht wordt uitgeoefend, maar ook in het belang van alle lidstaten die de controles aan de binnengrenzen hebben afgeschaft. De lidstaten zouden er daarom voor moeten zorgen dat de maatregelen aan de buitengrenzen worden gecoördineerd om zo de goede werking van het Schengengebied te garanderen. Daartoe zouden de lidstaten vanaf 1 juli 2021 voor de ingezetenen van de derde landen die worden genoemd in bijlage I bij de aanbeveling van de Raad — speciale administratieve regio's en andere territoriale entiteiten en autoriteiten — als gewijzigd bij deze aanbeveling, de tijdelijke beperking van niet-essentiële reizen naar de EU op gecoördineerde wijze en geleidelijk moeten opheffen.

The states would therefore have to ensure that the measures at the external borders are coordinated in order to ensure the good functioning of the Schengen area. To this end, the states would have to from July 1, 2021, for the third countries listed in Annex I to the proposal — special administrative regions and other territorial entities and authorities and institutions — modify the temporary restriction on non-essential travel to the EU in a coordinated and gradual manner.
reference_response: Border controls are not only in the interest of the Member State on whose external borders they are exercised, but also in the interest of all Member States that have abolished controls at their internal borders. Therefore, Member States should ensure that measures at external borders are coordinated in order to ensure the proper functioning of the Schengen area. To this end, Member States should lift the temporary restriction on non-essential travel to the EU from the residents of the third countries listed in Annex I to the Council Recommendation — special administrative regions and other territorial entities and authorities — as amended by this Recommendation, in a coordinated and gradual manner, from 1 July 2021.

Replacing the tenth, this tax must finance the repayment of the public debt until the ordinary revenues of the state can cover the expenses of the state: it lasts in reality until 1789, and even is completed by a second (1756), and a third "twentyth" (1759-1763).

In dat geval kan sprake zijn van een ziekte van het beenmerg, of aantasting van het beenmerg door bijvoorbeeld chemotherapie. Het kan echter ook zijn de nieren onvoldoende erytropoëtine aanmaken. However, it could also be a deficiency in erythropoietin production in the kidneys.
reference_response: If someone with anemia has a normal or even reduced number of reticulocytes in the blood, it is a sign that something is wrong with the production of blood cells in the bone marrow. However, it could also be that the kidneys are not producing enough erythropoietin. Vitamin B12 and folic acid are necessary for the production of reticulocytes.

reference_response: In Antarctica, all eyes are on Thwaites. This giant glacier, which covers 192,000 square kilometers (twenty-two times the size of Corsica), has been undergoing accelerated melting for half a century. prompt: Wien, 12. Jänner 2017 –„Unser solidarisches Gesundheitswesen verpflichtet die Versicherten und die Krankenkassen zur gegenseitigen Leistungserbringung. Daher ist es für die Kassen durchaus legitim, Reserven aufzubauen. Dies darf aber keinesfalls dazu führen, dass nur noch gespart wird, während Leistungen für die Versicherten gekürzt werden. Und dies, obwohl Milliarden an Rücklagen bestehen“, so Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, Generalsekretär der Pharmig. „Die Forderung von Bundeskanzler Kern, die 3 Milliarden Euro Rücklagen der Sozialversicherung an die Versichertengemeinschaft zurückzuführen, unterstützen wir daher ohne Einschränkung.“
model_response: Vienna, January 12, 2017 – The health care system of solidarity is obligated to the insured and the insurance companies to provide mutual support. Therefore, it is legitimate to build up reserves. However, this cannot lead to that only savings are preserved, while the services for the insured are reduced. And this, despite that there are billions of reserves, “as Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, General Secretary of the Pharmig, said. “The call of Chancellor Kern to return the 3 billion euros of the social security fund to the insured community is supported without any restriction.”
reference_response: Vienna, 12 January 2017 – “Our solidarity-based healthcare system obliges insured parties and health insurance companies to provide services to each other. Therefore, it is entirely legitimate for the insurance companies to build up reserves. However, this must not lead to a situation where savings are made at the expense of services for insured parties, even though billions in reserves exist”, says Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, General Secretary of Pharmig. “We therefore fully support the demand by Federal Chancellor Kern to return the 3 billion euro in reserves from social insurance to the insured community.”

prompt: Existem outros efeitos complicadores como a competição entre as diferentes causas de morte. Dentre as doenças respiratórias o mesmo fenômeno pode ocorrer com picos de situações muito adversas antecipando óbitos que, em condições normais, só iriam ocorrer alguns dias depois. O que acontece é que esses dias posteriores apresentam uma incidência que é enganadoramente baixa, pois as pessoas com desfechos que iriam aparecer nesses dias apareceram inadvertidamente em algum dia anterior. Esse fenômeno é conhecido com efeito colheita. Seu tratamento estatístico está longe de ser trivial.
model_response: There are other complicating factors such as the competition between different causes of death. Sometimes, heart attacks can steal from the respiratory diseases, people that were destined to die from them. The same phenomenon can occur with very bad situations, where the deaths that would have occurred a few days later would have happened in the days that followed. What happens is that those days that follow are actually having a much lower incidence, because the people who would have died in those days appeared unexpectedly in some days before. This phenomenon is known as the "falling knife". Its statistical treatment is not trivial.
reference_response: There are other complicating effects such as competition between different causes of death. Sometimes, heart attacks can steal from respiratory diseases people who were destined to die due to their harmful effects. Among respiratory diseases, the same phenomenon can occur with spikes in very adverse situations, bringing forward deaths that, under normal conditions, would only occur a few days later. What happens is that these later days have an incidence that is deceptively low, because people with outcomes that would appear on these days appeared inadvertently on some previous day. This phenomenon is known as the harvest effect. Its statistical treatment is far from trivial.

prompt: La Xylella fastidiosa è un batterio trasmesso dagli insetti e colpisce diverse piantagioni, come ulivi, agrumi, mandorli, uva, caffè e pesche. Il suo effetto consiste nel bloccare l’assorbimento delle sostanze nutritive e dell’acqua da parte delle piante fino a causarne la morte. Il Centro comune di ricerca della Commissione Europea ha stimato che la piena diffusione della malattia potrebbe costare all’UE 5,5 miliardi di euro all’anno, a causa della perdita di produzioni e piantagioni, a cui vanno aggiunti 0,7 miliardi di euro per via delle perdite legate alle esportazioni e 300.000 posti di lavoro.
model_response: Xylella fastidiosa is a bacterium transmitted by insects and affects various plant diseases such as olive trees, citrus fruits, almonds, grapes, coffee and peaches. Its effect is to block the uptake of nutrients and water from the plants until it causes their death. The European Commission’s Common Research Centre estimated that the full spread of the disease would cost the EU 5.5 billion euros per year, due to the loss of production and plantations, as well as 0.7 billion euros for exports and 300,000 jobs lost due to losses related to exports and 0.7 billion euros for the loss of production and plantations.
reference_response: Xylella fastidiosa is a bacterium transmitted by insects that affects various crops, such as olives, citrus fruits, almonds, grapes, coffee, and peaches. Its effect is to block the absorption of nutrients and water by the plants, leading to their death. The European Commission's Joint Research Centre has estimated that the full spread of the disease could cost the EU 5.5 billion euros per year, due to the loss of production and plantations, to which must be added 0.7 billion euros due to losses related to exports and 300,000 jobs.

prompt: Não há uma resposta simples para explicar por que as aplicações da física quântica aconteceram nos Estados Unidos. Mas foi fundamental ali o aparecimento de fábricas de ideia, entre elas o laboratório da Bell, que reunia engenheiros, técnicos e cientistas notáveis com sólida formação básica, e onde Bardeen, Shockley e Brattain tiveram a ideia de desenvolver o transistor. Os três ganharam o Prêmio Nobel de Física por isso e Bardeen, mais tarde, ganhou o segundo Nobel em física pela supercondutividade.
model_response: There is no simple answer to why quantum physics happened in the United States. But it was fundamental there the emergence of quantum computing facilities, such as the Bell laboratory, which brought together engineers, technicians, and scientists with basic education, and where Bardeen, Shockley and Brattain had the idea of developing the transistor. The three of them won the Nobel Prize in Physics for this and Bardeen later won the second Nobel Prize in Physics for superconductivity.
reference_response: There is no simple answer to explain why the applications of quantum physics occurred in the United States. But a key factor was the emergence of idea factories, among them the Bell laboratory, which brought together notable engineers, technicians, and scientists with a solid basic education, and where Bardeen, Shockley, and Brattain came up with the idea to develop the transistor. The three won the Nobel Prize in Physics for this, and Bardeen later won a second Nobel in physics for superconductivity.

prompt: Il D.Lgs 81/08 prevede che tutti i dipendenti devono essere adeguatamente formati sull’utilizzo corretto e sicuro di un trapano a colonne prima dell’inizio della loro attività lavorativa. È fondamentale che si comprendano gli effetti potenzialmente pericolosi, come la possibilità di lesionarsi con il movimento rotatorio o con le lame taglienti. I formatori dovrebbero spiegare i principali elementi di una procedura di utilizzo sicura, come indossare sempre guanti da lavoro e occhiali protettivi, non toccare mai le parti in movimento durante il funzionamento, inserire la fresa nella posizione giusta ed evitare cambiamenti improvvisi nelle impostazioni del macchinario. Questa formazione fornirà al personale le competenze necessarie per operare in modo responsabile e produttivo con un dispositivo così potente ed efficace.
model_response: The L. 81/08 law prescribes that all employees must be properly trained on the correct and safe use of a rotating column plier before starting their work. It is essential that they understand the potential hazards, such as the risk of injury from movement or the cutting blades. The trainers must explain the main elements of a safe use procedure, such as wearing protective gloves and safety glasses, never touching the parts in motion during operation, inserting the plier in the correct position, and avoiding sudden changes in the machine settings. This training will provide the necessary skills for the employees to operate the device in a responsible and productive manner with such a powerful and effective device.
reference_response: The D.Lgs 81/08 states that all employees must be adequately trained on the correct and safe use of a pillar drill before the start of their working activity. It is essential that they understand the potentially hazardous effects, such as the possibility of injury from rotating movement or sharp blades. Trainers should explain the main elements of a safe use procedure, such as always wearing work gloves and protective glasses, never touching moving parts during operation, inserting the drill bit in the correct position and avoiding sudden changes in the machine settings. This training will provide staff with the necessary skills to operate responsibly and productively with such a powerful and effective device.

prompt: Grenstoezicht is niet alleen in het belang van de lidstaat aan de buitengrenzen waarvan het toezicht wordt uitgeoefend, maar ook in het belang van alle lidstaten die de controles aan de binnengrenzen hebben afgeschaft. De lidstaten zouden er daarom voor moeten zorgen dat de maatregelen aan de buitengrenzen worden gecoördineerd om zo de goede werking van het Schengengebied te garanderen. Daartoe zouden de lidstaten vanaf 1 juli 2021 voor de ingezetenen van de derde landen die worden genoemd in bijlage I bij de aanbeveling van de Raad — speciale administratieve regio's en andere territoriale entiteiten en autoriteiten — als gewijzigd bij deze aanbeveling, de tijdelijke beperking van niet-essentiële reizen naar de EU op gecoördineerde wijze en geleidelijk moeten opheffen.
model_response: Grenzoverzicht is not only in the interest of the state bordering countries but also in the interest of all states that have abolished border controls. The states would therefore have to ensure that the measures at the external borders are coordinated in order to ensure the good functioning of the Schengen area. To this end, the states would have to adjust the third countries listed in Annex I of the proposal — special administrative regions and other territorial entities and authorities — from July 1, 2021, the temporary restriction on non-essential travel to the EU on a coordinated and gradual basis.
reference_response: Border controls are not only in the interest of the Member State on whose external borders they are exercised, but also in the interest of all Member States that have abolished controls at their internal borders. Therefore, Member States should ensure that measures at external borders are coordinated in order to ensure the proper functioning of the Schengen area. To this end, Member States should lift the temporary restriction on non-essential travel to the EU from the residents of the third countries listed in Annex I to the Council Recommendation — special administrative regions and other territorial entities and authorities — as amended by this Recommendation, in a coordinated and gradual manner, from 1 July 2021.

Remplaçant le dixième, cette redevance doit financer le remboursement de la dette publique jusqu’à ce que les revenus ordinaires suffisent à couvrir les dépenses de l’Etat : elle perdure en réalité jusqu’en 1789, et se trouve même complétée par un deuxième (1756), puis un troisième vingtième (1759-1763).

Replacing the tenth, this tax must finance the repayment of the public debt until the ordinary revenues of the state can cover the expenses of the state: it lasts in reality until 1789, and even is completed by a second (1756), and a third "twentyth" (1759-1763).

The evolution of poverty rates depends on the inflation rate, "that would imply that poverty in the country has increased by 6.6 percentage points", according to the Financial Times.
reference_response: The report by the National Institute of Statistics of Rwanda (NISR), published before the referendum, indicated that the proportion of poor inhabitants had decreased from 44.9% in 2011 to 39.1% in 2014. However, "between 2011 and 2014, the cost of products increased by at least 30%", estimates Sam Desiere, a researcher at the University of Louvain (Belgium). prompt: Wien, 12. Jänner 2017 –„Unser solidarisches Gesundheitswesen verpflichtet die Versicherten und die Krankenkassen zur gegenseitigen Leistungserbringung. Daher ist es für die Kassen durchaus legitim, Reserven aufzubauen. Dies darf aber keinesfalls dazu führen, dass nur noch gespart wird, während Leistungen für die Versicherten gekürzt werden. Und dies, obwohl Milliarden an Rücklagen bestehen“, so Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, Generalsekretär der Pharmig. „Die Forderung von Bundeskanzler Kern, die 3 Milliarden Euro Rücklagen der Sozialversicherung an die Versichertengemeinschaft zurückzuführen, unterstützen wir daher ohne Einschränkung.“
model_response: Vienna, January 12, 2017 –„Our health care system is committed to the solidarity of the insured and the health insurance companies to provide mutual support. Therefore, it is legitimate for the health insurance companies to build up reserves. However, this cannot lead to that only savings are preserved, while the services for the insured are reduced. And this, despite the billions of euros in reserves,“ said Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, General Secretary of the Pharmig. „The call of Chancellor Kern to return the 3 billion euros of the social security fund to the insured community is supported without any limitations.“
reference_response: Vienna, 12 January 2017 – “Our solidarity-based healthcare system obliges insured parties and health insurance companies to provide services to each other. Therefore, it is entirely legitimate for the insurance companies to build up reserves. However, this must not lead to a situation where savings are made at the expense of services for insured parties, even though billions in reserves exist”, says Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, General Secretary of Pharmig. “We therefore fully support the demand by Federal Chancellor Kern to return the 3 billion euro in reserves from social insurance to the insured community.”

prompt: Existem outros efeitos complicadores como a competição entre as diferentes causas de morte. Dentre as doenças respiratórias o mesmo fenômeno pode ocorrer com picos de situações muito adversas antecipando óbitos que, em condições normais, só iriam ocorrer alguns dias depois. O que acontece é que esses dias posteriores apresentam uma incidência que é enganadoramente baixa, pois as pessoas com desfechos que iriam aparecer nesses dias apareceram inadvertidamente em algum dia anterior. Esse fenômeno é conhecido com efeito colheita. Seu tratamento estatístico está longe de ser trivial.
model_response: There are other complicating factors such as the competition between different causes of death. Sometimes, heart attacks can steal from the respiratory diseases, people who were destined to die from them. The same phenomenon can occur with very bad situations, which would normally only occur a few days later. What happens is that the days that follow are actually much more frequent, because the people who would have died from these situations appeared unexpectedly in some days before. This phenomenon is known as the "falling leaf" effect. Its statistical treatment is not trivial.
reference_response: There are other complicating effects such as competition between different causes of death. Sometimes, heart attacks can steal from respiratory diseases people who were destined to die due to their harmful effects. Among respiratory diseases, the same phenomenon can occur with spikes in very adverse situations, bringing forward deaths that, under normal conditions, would only occur a few days later. What happens is that these later days have an incidence that is deceptively low, because people with outcomes that would appear on these days appeared inadvertently on some previous day. This phenomenon is known as the harvest effect. Its statistical treatment is far from trivial.

prompt: Halverwege de middag komen we aan in Boujdour, waar we een hotel zoeken. Het woestijnstadje telt zo'n 40.000 inwoners en ligt in het door Marokko bezette deel van de Westelijke Sahara, een gebied met een half miljoen inwoners. Tot 1975 was het een kolonie van Spanje. Daarna werd de Westelijke Sahara ingelijfd door Marokko, maar in 1976 werd de 'Arabische Democratische Republiek Sahara' (ADRS) uitgeroepen als een onafhankelijke staat. Het grootste gedeelte van het gebied wordt bestuurd door Marokko. Betekent dit dat we nog steeds in Marokko zijn of zijn we hier in de ADRS of heet het hier West-Sahara? Het is me niet helemaal duidelijk, maar één ding weet ik wel zeker: we zijn in de woestijn.

The desert town has a population of 40,000 and lies in the Moroccan-occupied part of the Western Sahara, a region with a half million inhabitants. Until 1975 it was a Spanish colony. Then the Western Sahara was annexed by Morocco, but in 1976 the 'Arab Democratic Republic of Sahara' (ADRS) was proclaimed as an independent state. The majority of the territory is under the control of Morocco. This means that we are still in Morocco or are we in the ADRS or is it West Sahara? It's not entirely clear to me, but one thing is certain: we are in the desert.
reference_response: In the middle of the afternoon we arrive in Boujdour, where we look for a hotel. The desert town has about 40,000 inhabitants and is located in the part of Western Sahara occupied by Morocco, an area with half a million inhabitants. Until 1975 it was a colony of Spain. After that, Western Sahara was annexed by Morocco, but in 1976 the 'Arab Democratic Republic of Sahara' (ADRS) was proclaimed as an independent state. The largest part of the area is governed by Morocco. Does this mean that we are still in Morocco or are we here in the ADRS or is it called Western Sahara here? It is not entirely clear to me, but one thing I am sure of: we are in the desert.

reference_response: In 1965, they received their first record contract on the prestigious Polydor label and not long after, their debut album Just Ear-rings was released, featuring their first hit single Please Go. prompt: La Xylella fastidiosa è un batterio trasmesso dagli insetti e colpisce diverse piantagioni, come ulivi, agrumi, mandorli, uva, caffè e pesche. The European Commission’s Common Research Centre estimated that the full spread of the disease would cost the EU 5.5 billion euros per year, due to the loss of production and plantations, as well as 0.7 billion euros for exports and 300,000 jobs lost due to losses related to exports and 0.7 billion euros for the loss of production and plantations.
reference_response: Xylella fastidiosa is a bacterium transmitted by insects that affects various crops, such as olives, citrus fruits, almonds, grapes, coffee, and peaches. Its effect is to block the absorption of nutrients and water by the plants, leading to their death. The European Commission's Joint Research Centre has estimated that the full spread of the disease could cost the EU 5.5 billion euros per year, due to the loss of production and plantations, to which must be added 0.7 billion euros due to losses related to exports and 300,000 jobs.

But a key factor was the emergence of idea factories, among them the Bell laboratory, which brought together notable engineers, technicians, and scientists with a solid basic education, and where Bardeen, Shockley, and Brattain came up with the idea to develop the transistor. prompt: Grenstoezicht is niet alleen in het belang van de lidstaat aan de buitengrenzen waarvan het toezicht wordt uitgeoefend, maar ook in het belang van alle lidstaten die de controles aan de binnengrenzen hebben afgeschaft. De lidstaten zouden er daarom voor moeten zorgen dat de maatregelen aan de buitengrenzen worden gecoördineerd om zo de goede werking van het Schengengebied te garanderen. Daartoe zouden de lidstaten vanaf 1 juli 2021 voor de ingezetenen van de derde landen die worden genoemd in bijlage I bij de aanbeveling van de Raad — speciale administratieve regio's en andere territoriale entiteiten en autoriteiten — als gewijzigd bij deze aanbeveling, de tijdelijke beperking van niet-essentiële reizen naar de EU op gecoördineerde wijze en geleidelijk moeten opheffen.
model_response: Grenzoverzicht is not only in the interest of the state bordering countries but also in the interest of all states that have abolished border controls. The states would therefore have to ensure that the measures at the external borders are coordinated in order to ensure the good functioning of the Schengen area. To this end, the states would have to adjust the third countries listed in Annex I of the proposal — special administrative regions and other territorial entities and authorities — from July 1, 2021, the temporary restriction on non-essential travel to the EU on a coordinated and gradual basis.
reference_response: Border controls are not only in the interest of the Member State on whose external borders they are exercised, but also in the interest of all Member States that have abolished controls at their internal borders. Therefore, Member States should ensure that measures at external borders are coordinated in order to ensure the proper functioning of the Schengen area. To this end, Member States should lift the temporary restriction on non-essential travel to the EU from the residents of the third countries listed in Annex I to the Council Recommendation — special administrative regions and other territorial entities and authorities — as amended by this Recommendation, in a coordinated and gradual manner, from 1 July 2021.

In 1828 the then owner and occupier Edmond Willem van Dam of Isselt of the house renovated the original building in a significant way. Later was the house "Groot Ravenstein" called, in contrast to "Klein Ravenstein" in Buurmalsen. On 4 April 1916 it was sold to the public and shortly afterwards demolished. prompt: Según los expertos, un factor a tener en cuenta es que los niños que desayunan generalmente comen más nutrientes básicos que los que no lo hacen. En concreto, varios estudios revelan que cuando los escolares no tienen suficiente hierro en la sangre les cuesta mucho prestar atención y concentrarse, se vuelven irritables, tienen dificultades de percepción, bajan sus calificaciones en pruebas de inteligencia (especialmente en vocabulario) y su rendimiento general se ve afectado.

The main factors that reduce the school performance of children is that they skip one of the three main meals (breakfast, lunch, and dinner), that they do not eat enough iron, and that they are exposed to lead. In particular, several studies show that when children do not have enough iron in their blood, they are much more distracted, irritable, have difficulty perceiving, and their overall performance is affected.
reference_response: According to experts, one factor to consider is that children who eat breakfast generally consume more basic nutrients than those who do not. The main factors that reduce children's school performance are skipping any of the three main meals (breakfast, lunch, and dinner), eating little iron, and being exposed to lead. Specifically, several studies reveal that when schoolchildren do not have enough iron in their blood, they have a hard time paying attention and concentrating, they become irritable, have perception difficulties, their grades drop in intelligence tests (especially in vocabulary), and their overall performance is affected.

reference_response: The report by the National Institute of Statistics of Rwanda (NISR), published before the referendum, indicated that the proportion of poor inhabitants had decreased from 44.9% in 2011 to 39.1% in 2014. prompt: Wien, 12. Jänner 2017 –„Unser solidarisches Gesundheitswesen verpflichtet die Versicherten und die Krankenkassen zur gegenseitigen Leistungserbringung. Daher ist es für die Kassen durchaus legitim, Reserven aufzubauen. Dies darf aber keinesfalls dazu führen, dass nur noch gespart wird, während Leistungen für die Versicherten gekürzt werden. Und dies, obwohl Milliarden an Rücklagen bestehen“, so Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, Generalsekretär der Pharmig. „Die Forderung von Bundeskanzler Kern, die 3 Milliarden Euro Rücklagen der Sozialversicherung an die Versichertengemeinschaft zurückzuführen, unterstützen wir daher ohne Einschränkung.“
model_response: Vienna, January 12, 2017 –„Our health care system is committed to the solidarity of the insured and the health insurance companies to provide mutual support. Therefore, it is legitimate for the health insurance companies to build up reserves. However, this cannot lead to that only savings are preserved, while services for the insured are reduced. And this, despite the billions of euros in reserves,“ said Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, General Secretary of the Pharmig. „The call of Chancellor Kern to return the 3 billion euros of the social security fund to the insured community is supported without any limitations.“
reference_response: Vienna, 12 January 2017 – “Our solidarity-based healthcare system obliges insured parties and health insurance companies to provide services to each other. Therefore, it is entirely legitimate for the insurance companies to build up reserves. However, this must not lead to a situation where savings are made at the expense of services for insured parties, even though billions in reserves exist”, says Dr. Jan Oliver Huber, General Secretary of Pharmig. “We therefore fully support the demand by Federal Chancellor Kern to return the 3 billion euro in reserves from social insurance to the insured community.”

O que acontece é que esses dias posteriores apresentam uma incidência que é enganadoramente baixa, pois as pessoas com desfechos que iriam aparecer nesses dias apareceram inadvertidamente em algum dia anterior. What happens is that the days that follow are actually much more frequent, because the people who would have died from these situations appeared unexpectedly in some days before. This phenomenon is known as the "falling leaf" effect. Its statistical treatment is not trivial.
reference_response: There are other complicating effects such as competition between different causes of death. Sometimes, heart attacks can steal from respiratory diseases people who were destined to die due to their harmful effects.
